article.headline: Xavier 105, Fordham 58
article.story: CINCINNATI -- Jordan Crawford scored 23 points with several impressive drives to the basket on Sunday, and Jamel McLean and Kenny Frease dominated inside, leading Xavier to a 108-60 victory over Fordham that extended its home-court success. Xavier (15-6, 7-1 Atlantic 10 Conference) has won its last 21 home games, the fifth-longest active streak in Division I. The Musketeers have won 29 straight A10 home games, the second-longest streak in league history -- five shy of Temple's record. Crawford, the league's top scorer at 19 points per game, went 7 of 11 from the field. McLean added 16 points and seven rebounds, and Frease scored 14 with eight rebounds. Terrell Holloway had a career-high 10 assists. Brenton Butler scored 26 and Chris Gaston added 23 for Fordham (2-18, 0-8), which has lost 13 in a row.
